---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof vs Judge.me — Which Review App Is Right for Your Store? | SocialProof" description="Comparing SocialProof vs Judge.me? Judge.me is built for product reviews on Shopify. SocialProof collects service testimonials for any website. Here's the honest difference.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        SocialProof vs Judge.me
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Judge.me is an excellent product review app for Shopify merchants. SocialProof is built for service businesses and brands that want to collect testimonials about their company — not individual product SKUs. Here's the honest breakdown.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What Judge.me does well</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li>Product-level reviews tightly integrated with Shopify product pages</li>
        <li>Automatic review request emails after order fulfillment</li>
        <li>Photo and video reviews for e-commerce products</li>
        <li>Shopify star ratings in Google Shopping results</li>
        <li>Review import from other Shopify review apps</li>
        <li>Affordable pricing for high-volume Shopify stores</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Where Judge.me falls short for service businesses</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Shopify-only:</strong> Judge.me requires Shopify. If you're on WordPress, Webflow, Squarespace, or a custom site, it doesn't apply.</li>
        <li><strong>Product-centric data model:</strong> Reviews are attached to product SKUs. There's no way to collect testimonials about your overall service, team, or experience.</li>
        <li><strong>No service business workflows:</strong> No intake forms, no "about us" or service page testimonial widgets, no review sequences for repeat clients.</li>
        <li><strong>Not built for personal services:</strong> A salon, coach, or consultant doesn't have "products" to review — Judge.me's model doesn't fit.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What SocialProof does differently</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Works on any website</strong> — Shopify, WordPress, Webflow, Squarespace, Wix, custom HTML, or anything with an embed code.</li>
        <li><strong>Service & experience testimonials</strong> — collect feedback about your business, your team, your process, not just individual products.</li>
        <li><strong>Flexible collection</strong> — shareable link, embedded form, or email sequence. No Shopify order trigger required.</li>
        <li><strong>Display anywhere</strong> — homepage, about page, services page, checkout flow, landing pages. One widget, many placements.</li>
        <li><strong>Works for any business model</strong> — coaches, consultants, agencies, local services, SaaS, restaurants, and yes, Shopify stores that want brand-level testimonials too.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Side-by-side comparison</h2>
      <div style="overflow-x:auto;margin-top:1rem;">
        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:0.95rem;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background:#f1f5f9;">
              <th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Feature</th>
              <th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Judge.me</th>
              <th style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;text-align:left;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">SocialProof</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Platform support</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Shopify only</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Any website</td></tr>
            <tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Review type</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Product reviews</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Service & brand testimonials</td></tr>
            <tr><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Collection trigger</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Post-order email</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Shareable link, form, or email</td></tr>
            <tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Works for services</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">No</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Yes — built for this</td></tr>
            <tr><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Free tier</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Yes (limited)</td><td style="padding:0.75rem 1rem;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Free forever for 1 active widget</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Which should you choose?</h2>
      <p><strong>Choose Judge.me</strong> if you're a Shopify merchant and your primary goal is product-level reviews attached to product pages and Google Shopping.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong>Choose SocialProof</strong> if you want testimonials about your brand, service, or team — regardless of what platform you're on. If you're not on Shopify, or if you want to collect and display "here's why I love this company" testimonials rather than product star ratings, SocialProof is the right tool.</p>

      <div style="margin-top:2.5rem;text-align:center;">
        <a href="/signup" style="display:inline-block;background:#2563eb;color:white;padding:0.85rem 2.2rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">
          Try SocialProof free
        </a>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.9rem;color:#888;">Free forever for 1 active widget. No credit card.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
